[2] Trinidad
Date: Tue 22 Jan 2008
Source: Trinidad and Tobago Express [edited]
<http://www.trinidadexpress.com/index.pl/article_news?id=161267456>

Health officials have been sent to communities in Chaguanas to investigate
a possible dengue outbreak in the Borough. A Health Ministry official said
yesterday [21 Jan 2008] that 6 residents had reportedly contracted dengue
fever but "we have no details on this so we sent a team to gather
information and assess how serious the problem was."
Chaguanas mayor Surujrattan Rambachan said information from Surveillance
Nurse of County Caroni, Cecile Johnson-David, indicated that the outbreak
required urgent attention. He said laboratory tests have confirmed that the
6 patients had contracted dengue fever. The affected patients live along
the Longdenville Main Road, Cunupia; Ragoonanan Road, Enterprise; Kinnow
Crescent, Orchard Gardens, and Franz Gardens, Orchard Gardens. Rambachan
has launched a campaign to rid the borough of empty containers and tyres
after 6 cases of dengue fever were recorded at the district health facility.
[byline: Carolyn Kissoon]
--
