[7] Venezuela: (Trujillo)
Date: Sat 26 Jan 2007
Source: Diario El Tempo [in Spanish, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.diarioeltiempo.com.ve/secciones/secciones.php?num=1405&anon=n2008&codigo=nreg&llve=tres>

Dengue threatens Trujillo residents
-----------------------------------
In the last 3 weeks [of January 2008] 244 dengue cases have been reported
of which 242 are classical dengue and 2 are DHF, without counting
unreported cases.
There has been a fight against dengue in the state since August [2007], and
when the year closed there were reported 2717 dengue cases in the state, of
which 85 were DHF according to epidemiologist Martiza Garcia of the
regional health system.
[This article goes on to report that local health and community leaders met
to plan a response for dengue control, with emphasis on elimination of
mosquito vector breeding sites. - Mod.TY]
