[14] Philippines: (Rizal)
Date: Thu 24 Jan 2008
Source: GMA News TV [edited]
<http://www.gmanews.tv/story/77792/Valenzuela-troubled-by-steep-rise-in-dengue-cases>

Valenzuela troubled by steep rise in dengue cases
-------------------------------------------------
A steep rise in dengue cases in Valenzuela City had been monitored during
the first 3 weeks of January [2008] -- a whopping 90 per cent increase in
the number of reported cases compared to the figures from the same period
last year [2007].
Radio dzBB reported Thursday [24 Jan 2008] that the Valenzuela City
government has already recorded 25 dengue cases from 1-19 Jan [2008], most
of which were recorded in Barangays [neighborhoods] Rincon and Gen T de Leon.
This steep increase in dengue cases jolted the city government into
intensifying its information and cleanup drive against the potentially
fatal illness. The Valenzuela City government started Wednesday [23 Jan
2008] an intensive campaign to residents to clean their surroundings, after
health officials voiced alarm over the sudden rise in dengue cases.
Valenzuela City epidemiologist Manuel Mapue appealed to local residents to
rely on themselves instead of the government to avoid acquiring the
disease. This, even as the city government ordered a door-to-door campaign
encouraging residents to keep their surroundings clean and dry, to prevent
dengue-carrying mosquitoes from breeding.
Since last year [2007], health authorities had declared dengue a year-round
threat, not just during the rainy season. They also warned against
unnecessary fogging operations, which they said may just drive mosquitoes
to other areas.
--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail rapporteur Brent Barrett
[Fogging could provide short-term interruption of dengue virus
transmission; long-term vector mosquito population reduction requires the
elimination of water catchments that providing mosquito breeding sites. An
interactive map showing the location of Valenzuela City in Rizal province,
and of that province in the Philippines can be accessed at
<http://www.fallingrain.com/world/RP/53/Valenzuela.html>. - Mod.TY]
